4:
Tch... Those blasted Defaulters!
You! Get it ready!
6:
You're up, Techtus! Time to take out
the trash!
9: Th-there's just no way! I can't do it!
15:
A n-newbie like me? I don't stand a
chance!
18:
What, are all those weapons just for
show? What do you think we
recruited you for?!
22:
Recruited?! More like kidnapped! Er,
scammed, rather! I've been
scammed!
25:
You modified me while I was
unconscious! Took me to some
strange place! Where am I, huh?
HUH?!
42: Wh-why... Why me? It's not fair...
45:
I-I'm just a normal guy who likes
sitting around and playing video
games! How did I end up in this
nightmare?!
49:
Oh, wait. That's it, I'm dreaming! I
must have passed out after that
marathon gaming session, yeah!
62: That's why I need your help, Alk.
71:
That's my line! Where am I? Did I
die? Is this heaven! It's beautiful!
Wait, is that... grass? REAL grass?!
75:
Don't stop to smell the roses—it's
time to introduce yourself. If these
fine folk don't take a liking to you,
your next stop might just be the
junkyard!
79:
I don't think I really understand the
situation either, but... Well, here
goes...
85:
Despite my current appearance, I
was once a very ordinary individual.
88:
All my friends keep moving on up in
the world while I've enjoyed taking it
easy and having fun.
91:
But eventually I ran into the greatest
obstacle I've ever dealt with in life.
94:
"Oh crap... I spent too much! There's
almost nothing left in my account!"
95:
"And I've got that trip tomorrow!
Everyone's just going to leave me
behind again..."
98:
...Sh-shouldn't you have expected
this to happen?
103:
What was I supposed to do!? Having
friends is expensive! They'll toss you
aside if you can't keep up!
112:
I've been having enough trouble as
it is, but could you imagine if they
saw me looking like THIS?!
116:
But just when I was at my lowest, I
got a single message.
119:
"Congratulations! Thanks to your
developed sense of spatial
awareness, you've been selected for
a highly specialized job!"
120:
"The job description will be provided
at a later date. No experience or
qualifications are required. All
expenses will be covered..."
123: This is it! I thought to myself...
133:
I didn't think it over too hard at the
time... And like, even if it WAS a
scam, I thought my friends would
get a good laugh out of it!
137:
But then they turned me into this
thing! My entire body was modified
without my consent! They even
threw me onto the battlefield the
very next day!
141:
Sure, it was a wild experience, but
this sucks! I didn't sign up to be
traumatized like this!
144:
I don't even know where to start with
how awful this whole situation is...
148:
Returning you to your original body
will be extraordinarily expensive,
and the Updaters aren't going to let
you walk away for free, either.
152: I was broke enough to begin with!
161:
Don't worry. You can live here until
you find a way out of this mess.
169:
Yes. However, you must be more
careful the next ti—
174:
Oh, THANK you! You guys are
AWESOME! I'm blown away, thank
you!
179:
Y-yeah, no problem. But maybe you
should go back home at least once
first? Your friends might be
wondering about you—
184:
No way! I can't let them see me like
this!
188:
...Alk, how would you react if a good
friend of yours showed up one day
having suddenly been transformed
into an ultimate weapon?
192: I... I'd be confused, I guess... But still—
197: Right?! That's why I can't do it!
201:
What's happened to me... 
All I wanted was to hang out with
my friends!
217:
Whooaa! This is crazy! A real-life
fighting game?
221:
It's a pretty physical game, but it is a
GAME, not a duel to the death or
anyth—
227:
I'm entering as Techtus!
...Oh, you need my real name too?
Okay, it's Alvin Architect—
232:
Did you think about this at all?! This
is exactly what got you in trouble
last time!
239:
What a powerhouse! Our ironclad
newcomer Techtus might just be
invincible in the ring!
246:
That was a blast, and this new
frame of mine is insane! Everybody
was cheering me on, too!
250:
This is just the confidence boost I've
been needing! Man, I'm crazy hyped
right now!
254:
That's a relief. Seeing him at the end
of his rope weighed heavily on my
conscience, after all.
262:
By the way, we came to a mutual
agreement, and I obtained his
voiceprint as well. And I did tell him
to look over everything carefully.
265:
All I intended was to present him
with a path to change his
circumstances for the better,
though perhaps I was a little...
dramatic?
270:
All right, my mind's made up! I'm not
going home until I'm a certified
top-ranker in the ring!
